  <content contentuid="h5817b4acb9d14d88bd7ff166e1c72eaa4222" version="1">Complications</content>
  <content contentuid="h858c371dd6944b05a229e0f4962a4a13b996" version="1">Chance of</content>
  <content contentuid="h872389d9aca94b6597165fcab870a9dca37e" version="1">[5e] A complication might occur every workweek of scribing and when pausing for longer than twice the required time.</content>
  <content contentuid="he04986c0501b42e5a8dc68a404423dc7de9b" version="1">Complications won't occur during crafting.</content>
  <content contentuid="h8dff0f10029a49e7a3b44a86443d11acaa46" version="1">Chance of a scribing complication after every workweek.</content>
  <content contentuid="h43ed22f3563c4d0f90bda5defc375ec075a0" version="1">Quill Breaking</content>
  <content contentuid="haaa43064ee7f4245aae76eee03ad10a19612" version="1">Chance of breaking a quill after every full day of scribing.</content>
  <content contentuid="h3f65a838d1824f1b996d05d1149355a752d4" version="1">Scribing a spell scroll takes an amount of time and money related to the level of the spell the character wants to scribe, as shown in the Spell Scroll Costs table. In addition, the character must have proficiency in the Arcana skill and must provide any material components required for the casting of the spell. Moreover, the character must have the spell prepared, or it must be among the character's known spells, in order to scribe a scroll of that spell.&lt;br&gt;Crafting a spell scroll is a solitary task, unlikely to attract much attention. The complications that arise are more likely to involve the preparation needed for the activity. Every workweek spent scribing brings a 10 percent chance of a complication.</content>
